---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const selectedPackageReleaseTag = "v0.2.1";

const pythonFrontDoorSnippet = `import shardloom as sl

ctx = sl.context()
result = (
    ctx.read("data/orders.csv")
       .filter(sl.col("status") == "paid")
       .limit(10)
       .collect()
)

print(result.output_row_count)
print(result.first_result_row)
print(result.claim_summary.claim_gate_status)
print(result.fallback_attempted, result.external_engine_invoked)`;
---

<SiteLayout title="Start Local Proof" description="Run a local ShardLoom proof and inspect the selected package-release boundary." path="/start" active="start">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Start</p>
    <h1>Start local proof.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Use the source checkout, published {selectedPackageReleaseTag} package channels, local smokes, and checked-in evidence. The selected local/source/package v1 release track is GitHub prerelease + TestPyPI/PyPI + Homebrew.</p>
  </section>
  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>Recommended first route</h2>
      <p class="narrow">Install the package and CLI, run a normal Python read, then move to source-checkout proof when you need the full release validator stack.</p>
      <p class="narrow"><a href="https://github.com/depsilon/shardloom/blob/main/docs/getting-started/package-user-install.md">Package user install status</a> shows the {selectedPackageReleaseTag} GitHub pre-release, TestPyPI, PyPI, and Homebrew commands with channel proof refs. <a href="https://github.com/depsilon/shardloom/blob/main/docs/getting-started/source-checkout-install.md">Source checkout install</a> remains the strongest maintainer proof path.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="code-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">PowerShell</div>
      <pre><code>python scripts\release_dry_run_proof.py --rows 64 --iterations 1
python scripts\check_release_security_gate.py
python scripts\check_contribution_governance.py
python scripts\check_package_channel_readiness.py --require-local-evidence
python scripts\check_golden_workflows.py
python scripts\check_admitted_semantics_matrix.py
python scripts\check_release_architecture_tracker.py --allow-blocked
python scripts\final_release_rehearsal.py --allow-blocked
python scripts\check_website_readiness.py
python examples\local-python-smoke\run.py --repo-root .
python scripts\check_python_user_surface_completion.py
python scripts\check_v1_local_source_package_release.py
python scripts\check_production_usability_gate.py</code></pre>
      <div class="code-evidence"><span><strong>claim boundary</strong>local source-checkout proof</span><span><strong>fallback_attempted</strong>false where execution evidence is emitted</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>Support boundary</h2>
      <p class="narrow">Use the generated v1 support surface before assuming a path is live. Selected {selectedPackageReleaseTag} package channels are published; future package channels remain outside the selected release surface until their own proof exists.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="code-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Docs</div>
      <pre><code>docs/getting-started/v1-supported-unsupported.md
docs/getting-started/troubleshooting-support.md
docs/release/v1-local-source-package-release.md
package_install_commands_visible=true</code></pre>
      <div class="code-evidence"><span><strong>source</strong>runs-today + package-channel matrices</span><span><strong>support</strong>doctor/support-bundle JSON</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>Python front door</h2>
      <p class="narrow">The first Python smoke exercises the scoped local read/query path and prints the evidence fields that bound the claim. Source-checkout and benchmark examples may add explicit schemas, repo roots, and build profile order for reproducibility.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="code-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Python</div>
      <pre><code>{pythonFrontDoorSnippet}</code></pre>
      <div class="code-evidence"><span><strong>gate</strong>check_python_user_surface_completion.py</span><span><strong>scope</strong>admitted local runtime only</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <div class="route">
      <article class="route-step"><span>1</span><h3>Read the first proof</h3><p>Open the repository first-10-minutes guide for exact commands and expected outputs.</p></article>
      <article class="route-step"><span>2</span><h3>Run local evidence checks</h3><p>Use the repo scripts and contract tests; do not infer release/package status from local source execution.</p></article>
      <article class="route-step"><span>3</span><h3>Inspect boundaries</h3><p>Use the Field Guide limitations and benchmark methodology pages to distinguish admitted local proof from broader claims outside current evidence.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
